item.title: Funpk Problem
item.dc:creator: @bryanc Bryanc
item.description:
@bryanc wrote:

You are still not using the cases correctly.

You need to have it exactly like this: inFunPk()

Where ‘in’ is lowercase ‘F’ is uppercase ‘un’ is lowercase ‘P’ is uppercase and ‘k’ is lowercase.

If you have it in a different case setup, it will cause problems because it will not be existent in the cases you have. Like I said Java is case sensitive so it looks for things exactly how they are typed.
